# Security Standards

## Secrets Management
- Never hardcode secrets, API keys, or tokens in source code.
- Use `os.getenv()` with `python-dotenv` for all configuration. Reference `.env.example` for required variables.
- Never commit `.env` files. Only commit `.env.example` with placeholder values.

## Environment Variables
- All sensitive configuration must be loaded from environment variables.
- Document all required environment variables in `.env.example` with placeholder values.
- Use descriptive names for environment variables (e.g., `OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH`, `EMBEDDING_MODEL_NAME`, `VECTOR_STORE_PATH`).

## Local-First Privacy
- The system processes all data locally. No note content should be sent to external APIs in the MVP.
- Embedding models must run locally (no OpenAI API calls for embeddings unless the user explicitly opts in).
